@page "/drawer"
<PageTitle>Drawer - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="drawer">Drawer</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The Drawer component creates a side-panel layout with DrawerSide and
                DrawerContent children.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>&lt;Drawer&gt;
    &lt;DrawerSide&gt;
        Sidebar navigation here.
    &lt;/DrawerSide&gt;
    &lt;DrawerContent&gt;
        Main page content here.
    &lt;/DrawerContent&gt;
&lt;/Drawer&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="sub-components">Sub-components</h2>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr><th>Component</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td><code>&lt;DrawerSide&gt;</code></td><td>The sidebar/panel area.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>&lt;DrawerContent&gt;</code></td><td>The main content area next to the drawer.</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="drawer-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Drawer</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Drawer</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Bootstrap 5, the Drawer component is implemented using Bootstrap's offcanvas
                component. DrawerSide maps to the offcanvas panel and DrawerContent maps to the
                main page area. Opening and closing the drawer is handled via Bootstrap's
                offcanvas JavaScript API. The drawer can be positioned on the left, right, top,
                or bottom using Bootstrap's offcanvas placement modifier classes.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="drawer-daisyui">DaisyUI Drawer</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Drawer</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In DaisyUI, the Drawer component maps to DaisyUI's drawer class. DaisyUI's drawer
                is a CSS-only side panel controlled by a hidden checkbox input. DrawerSide maps to
                the drawer-side element and DrawerContent maps to the drawer-content element. The
                open state is toggled by checking or unchecking the associated input without any
                JavaScript interaction.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="drawer-basecoat">Basecoat Drawer</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Drawer</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Basecoat, the Drawer component is composed from Tailwind utility classes that
                create a side-panel layout using CSS transforms and transitions. DrawerSide
                receives absolute or fixed positioning utilities and a translate transform that
                slides it in and out of view. DrawerContent occupies the remaining page area.
                The open and closed states are controlled through a CSS class toggle.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("drawer", "Drawer"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("sub-components", "Sub-components", 2),
    new TocItem("drawer-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5 Drawer", 2),
    new TocItem("drawer-daisyui", "DaisyUI Drawer", 2),
    new TocItem("drawer-basecoat", "Basecoat Drawer", 2)
])" />

</div>
